properties.name: plot
properties.sample: Based on a true story, a 13-year-old boy who uses a wheelchair is determined to win a trophy like his athletic older brother.

properties.name: fullplot
properties.sample: Myron Yoder's Indiana family always was proud of eldest son Seth, a sports prodigy, but most attention goes to younger Justin, whose spina bifida condition means a wheelchair and constant, frantic care. During make-up chores for endangering grumpy neighbor Vic Sauder's sports car, Justin discovers a sport he finally hopes to excel in, soap box cart racing, and gets highly experienced Vic and pa to help and coach him. That proves promising and dangerous, but also puts unbearable stress on the family cohesion as Seth now feels cruelly shoved aside.

properties.name: consensus
properties.sample: This comedy is too slight to leave an impression, and its attempts at whimsy are not as funny as they could have been.
